tyle=\"background:seagreen;\"| WIN\n| IN\n| style=\"background:seagreen;\"| WIN\n| style=\"background:seagreen;\"| WIN\n| style=\"background:seagreen;\"| WIN\n| style=\"background:yellow;\"| LOW\n| style=\"background:crimson;\"| OUT\n| style=\"background:gray;\" colspan=\"1\"|\n|-\n! 4\n| Jasmine\n|{{stribe|eniledam|Pim\u00e2potew Kinosewak}}\n| style=\"background:seagreen;\"| WIN\n| style=\"background:seagreen;\"| WIN\n| IN\n| IN\n| style=\"background:yellow;\"| LOW\n| IN\n| IN\n| IN\n| style=\"background:seagreen;\"| WIN\n| IN\n| style=\"background:crimson;\"| OUT\n| style=\"background:gray;\" colspan=\"2\"|\n|-\n!rowspan=2| 6/5\n| Max\n|{{stribe|eniledam|Pim\u00e2potew Kinosewak }}\n| style=\"background:seagreen;\"| WIN\n| style=\"background:seagreen;\"| WIN\n| IN\n| IN\n| IN\n| style=\"background:yellow;\"| LOW\n| IN\n| style=\"background:seagreen;\"| WIN\n| IN\n| style=\"background:aqua;\"| DQ\n| style=\"background:gray;\" colspan=\"3\"|\n|-\n| Scarlett\n|{{stribe|eniledam|Pim\u00e2potew Kinosewak}}\n| style=\"background:seagreen;\"| WIN\n| style=\"background:seagreen;\"| WIN\n| IN\n| style=\"background:yellow;\"| LOW\n| IN\n| IN\n| IN\n| IN\n| IN\n| style=\"background:aqua;\"| DQ\n| style=\"background:gray;\" colspan=\"3\"|\n|-\n! 7\n| Dave\n|{{stribe|xhakum|Waneyihtam Maskwak}}\n| IN\n| IN\n| style=\"background:seagreen;\"| WIN\n| style=\"background:seagreen;\"| WIN\n| style=\"background:seagreen;\"| WIN\n| style=\"background:seagreen;\"| WIN\n| IN\n| style=\"background:seagreen;\"| WIN\n| style=\"background:crimson;\"| OUT\n| style=\"background:gray;\" colspan=\"4\"|\n|-\n! 8\n| Topher\n|{{stribe|eniledam|Pim\u00e2potew Kinosewak}}\n| style=\"background:seagreen;\"| WIN\n| style=\"background:seagreen;\"| WIN\n| IN\n| IN\n| IN\n| style=\"background:yellow;\"| LOW\n| IN\n| style=\"background:crimson;\"| OUT\n| style=\"background:gray;\" colspan=\"5\"|\n|-\n! 9\n| Ella\n|{{stribe|xhakum|Waneyihtam Maskwak}}\n| IN\n| style=\"background:yellow;\"| LOW\n| style=\"background:seagreen;\"| WIN\n| style=\"background:seagreen;\"| WIN\n| style=\"background:seagreen;\"| WIN\n| style=\"background:aqua;\"| DQ\n| style=\"background:gray;\" colspan=\"8\"|\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\" |11/10\n| Amy\n|{{stribe|eniledam|Pim\u00e2potew Kinosewak}}\n| style=\"background:seagreen;\" | WIN\n| style=\"background:seagreen;\" | WIN\n| style=\"background:crimson;\" | OUT\n| colspan=\"1\" style=\"background:gray;\" |\n| style=\"background:crimson;\" | OUT\n| colspan=\"8\" style=\"background:Gray;\" |\n|-\n| Samey\n|{{stribe|eniledam|Pim\u00e2potew Kinosewak}}\n| style=\"background:seagreen;\" | WIN\n| style=\"background:seagreen;\" | WIN\n| style=\"background:yellow;\" | LOW\n| IN\n| style=\"background:crimson;\" | OUT\n| colspan=\"9\" style=\"background:gray;\" |\n|-\n! 12\n| Rodney\n|{{stribe|eniledam|Pim\u00e2potew Kinosewak}}\n| style=\"background:seagreen;\" | WIN\n| style=\"background:seagreen;\" | WIN\n| IN\n| style=\"background:crimson;\" | OUT\n| colspan=\"10\" style=\"background:gray;\" |\n|-\n! 13\n| Leonard\n|{{stribe|xhakum|Waneyihtam Maskwak}}\n| style=\"background:yellow;\"| LOW\n| style=\"background:crimson;\"| OUT\n| style=\"background:gray;\" colspan=\"12\"|\n|-\n! 14\n| Beardo\n|{{stribe|xhakum|Waneyihtam Maskwak}}\n| style=\"background:crimson;\"| OUT\n| style=\"background:gray;\" colspan=\"13\"|\n|}\n\n==Characters==\n{{tone|section|date=December 2017}}\n{{original research section|date=December 2017}}\nThere are 28 characters overall who competed in this season. This sets the series record of having the most characters ever in a single season, the previous record being 22 characters in ''[[Total Drama Island]]''.\n\n===''Total Drama All-Stars''===\nSeven characters from ''[[Total Drama World Tour]]'' and seven characters from ''[[Total Drama: Revenge of the Island]]'' returned to compete in ''Total Drama All-Stars''. They all competed together during several \"Heroes vs. Villains\" themed challenges, which means that all the heroes competed against all the villains.<ref name=\"au\">[http://www.abc.net.au/abc3/studio3/ Interview with series creator, Tom McGillis] (Skip to 1:42) on video  {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121212045158/http://www.abc.net.au/abc3/studio3/ |date=December 12, 2012 }}</ref>\n\nThe fourteen returning characters who competed in ''Total Drama All-Stars'' are Alejandro, Cameron, Courtney, Duncan, Gwen, Heather, Jo, Lightning, Lindsay, Mike, Sam, Scott, Sierra, and Zoey.<ref name=\"cnallstars\">http://www.cartoonnetwork.com/cnservice/cartoonsvc/content/xml/getContentById.do?contentId=338850&depth=5</ref><ref name=\"tdas.pt1\">[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sjQ3MDAlnLM Total Drama All-Stars&nbsp;\u2013 Part 1]</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.followgram.me/i/482669631496432517_372348497 |title=Archived copy |access-date=August 9, 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130926160440/http://followgram.me/i/482669631496432517_372348497 |archive-date=September 26, 2013 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref name=\"tdas.pt2\">[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=r5uuIgMwrvE Total Drama All-Stars&nbsp;\u2013 Part 2]</ref> The winners are Mike and Zoey, both of them from the second generation cast and both on the Heroes team.\n\n====Main characters====\n[[File:MikeTD.png|thumb|right|A brief visual of Mike (on the left), four of his different personalities (in the middle), and Mal (on the right). Mike is the only male character in the series to have multiple animated versions in one body.]]\nMain characters appear in every episode of the segment they compete in:\n*'''Mike''' (labeled the ''Multiple Personality Disorder'')<ref name=\"freshtvinc.com\">{{cite web|url=http://www.freshtvinc.com/blog/total-drama-character-profiles-mike/ |title=Total Drama Character Profiles: Mike - Fresh TV |publisher=Freshtvinc.com |date=January 16, 2014 |accessdate=February 27, 2015}}</ref> is the winner in ''Total Drama All-Stars''. Mike is the only character in the whole series to have multiple voices in the same season all with the same voice actor. The animators had to illustrate five different faces and personalities in the character's body, making Mike the most complicated and diverse character in the series. [[Cory Doran]] had to record six different types of voices for Mike. In ''Total Drama All-Stars'', the character Mike serves as the season's protagonist, while his evil alternate personality, Mal (short for \"The Malevolent One\"), serves as the main antagonist. Mike's evil personality is a close reference to [[List of Yu-Gi-Oh! characters#Marik Ishtar / Yami Marik|Yami Marik]] from ''[[Yu-Gi-Oh!]]'', as both are evil split personalities who reside within a person and eventually take over their host, as well as undergoing a change in hairstyle and voice when assuming control. Mal's name and personality was also inspired by the character, Mal Cobb from the movie, ''[[Inception]]. Voiced by Cory Doran.\n*'''Zoey''' (labeled the ''Indie Chick'')<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.freshtvinc.com/blog/total-drama-character-profiles-zoey/ |title=Total Drama Character Profiles - Zoey - Fresh TV |publisher=Freshtvinc.com |date=January 21, 2014 |accessdate=February 27, 2015}}</ref> is one of the main characters of this season. Zoey is the runner-up of this season in Canada and the United States. Voiced by Barbara Mamabolo.\n\n====Other characters====\nOther than the main season winners, other characters from previous seasons also return in Part 1 of this season. Here is a list of all the characters as described by Teletoon for ''Total Drama All-Stars'':<ref name=\"teletoon.com\">{{cite web |url=http://www.teletoon.com/en/tv/totalDramaAllStars/ |title=Total Drama: Pahkitew Island |publisher=teletoon.com |accessdate=February 27, 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150206070400/http://www.teletoon.com/en/tv/totalDramaAllStars |archive-date=February 6, 2015 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n{{hidden begin|title=Returning from ''[[Total Drama World Tour]]''|titlestyle=text-align:left;}}\n*'''Alejandro''' ''(labeled the \"Arch Villain\")''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.freshtvinc.com/blog/total-drama-character-profiles-alejandro/ |title=Total Drama Character Profiles - Alejandro - Fresh TV |publisher=Freshtvinc.com |date=April 16, 2014 |accessdate=February 27, 2015}}</ref> is a dashing Spaniard, who is multitalented and irresistible to females just like Justin from Total Drama Island and Total Drama Action. He is a powerful manipulator. He is described as the villain with good looks. His ruthless, manipulative approach allowed him to plough through the third season and was the winner, however, his actions earned him huge karma and he didn't get to keep his winnings. His big brother and nemesis, Jos\u00e9, has the same personalities as Alejandro himself. Heather is also attracted to him, and vice versa. However, he was first introduced into the season as the Drama Machine, before he was later as Alejandro inside the robot suit. He received a new voice actor, [[Alex House]], in this new season, as his previous actor did not reprise the role for unexplained reasons. Voiced by Alex House.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.freshtvinc.com/blog/total-drama-all-stars-speculation/ |title=Total Drama All-Stars Speculation - Fresh TV |publisher=Freshtvinc.com |date=March 20, 2013 |accessdate=February 27, 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141207170408/http://www.freshtvinc.com/blog/total-drama-all-stars-speculation/ |archivedate=December 7, 2014 |df=mdy-all }}</ref>\n*'''Courtney''' ''(labeled the \"Type-A\")''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.freshtvinc.com/blog/total-drama-character-profiles-courtney/ |title=Total Drama Character Profiles - Courtney - Fresh TV |publisher=Freshtvinc.com |date=February 12, 2014 |accessdate=February 27, 2015}}</ref> is a close reference to [[Tracy Flick]] from [[Election (1999 film)|Election]]. She is a perfectionist who desires to be best at everything, and sees herself as a born leader. She believes in strictly following rules and sees herself as a good citizen, however her desire for success often clashes with her own principles. She can come off as being quite bossy and critical, which leads her to be disliked by many contestants. Her less likable side peaked in ''Total Drama Action'' where she served as the main antagonist. She formerly had a relationship with Duncan but broke up with him after three seasons, and later started a relationship with Scott, which ended in a matter of hours. Voiced by Emilie-Claire Barlow.\n*'''Duncan''' ''(labeled the \"Delinquent\")''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.freshtvinc.com/blog/total-drama-character-profiles-duncan/ |title=Total Drama Character Profiles - Duncan - Fresh TV |publisher=Freshtvinc.com |date=March 12, 2014 |accessdate=February 27, 2015}}</ref> is a tough, hardened ex-convict fresh out of [[youth detention center|juvie]]. He spends most of his time trying to looks tough and mean, or pranking others, however deep down he has a huge heart (which he tries very hard to hide). However this season his secret deep is discovered, which results in him being placed on the heroes team. He had a relationship with Gwen through the first 5 episodes, until she broke up with him. Before that he was in a relationship with Courtney, and although they broke up in season 3, he tried to win her back over the course of All-Stars. Voiced by Drew Nelson.\n*'''Gwen''' ''(labeled the \"Loner\")''<ref name=\"tv\" /> is very into [[Goth subculture]] and is Duncan's girlfriend until they broke up. She is desperately trying to make-up with Courtney for her betrayal and prove she's her friend and not a villain (with mixed results). Voiced by Meghan Fahlenbock.\n*'''Heather''' ''(labeled the \"Queen Bee\")''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.freshtvinc.com/blog/total-drama-character-profiles-heather/ |title=Total Drama Character Profiles - Heather - Fresh TV |publisher=Freshtvinc.com |date=March 5, 2014 |accessdate=February 27, 2015}}</ref> spends most of her time trying to force other characters to do what she wants. Despite this, she is a very strong competitor and has attraction with Alejandro. Voiced by Rachel Wilson.\n*'''Lindsay''' ''(labeled the \"Dumb Princess\")''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.freshtvinc.com/blog/total-drama-character-profiles-lindsay/ |title=Total Drama Character Profiles - Lindsay - Fresh TV |publisher=Freshtvinc.com |date=February 26, 2014 |accessdate=February 27, 2015}}</ref> is described as being beautiful, but not vain. While Lindsay is the prettiest one on the show and is spoilt silly by her father, she is kind-hearted and is able to make friends with almost everyone. However, her lack of intelligence often leads to her downfall, this season being no exception, where, despite being a fan favorite to make it far, she is the first to be eliminated. Voiced by Stephanie Anne Mills.\n*'''Sierra''' ''(labeled the \"Obsessive Uber-Fan\")''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.freshtvinc.com/blog/total-drama-character-profiles-sierra/ |title=Total Drama Character Profiles - Sierra - Fresh TV |publisher=Freshtvinc.com |date=February 19, 2014 |accessdate=February 27, 2015}}</ref> is the show's biggest fan and blogger. She is a parody of real life Total Drama fans. She is obsessed with every member of the cast, especially Cody whom she has an obsessive crush on. However, due to being deprived of Cody for too long, this season she begins to lose her sanity and starts seeing everyone else as Cody, especially Cameron. Voiced by Annick Obonsawin.\n{{hidden end}}\n{{hidden begin|title=Returning from ''[[Total Drama: Revenge of the Island]]''|titlestyle=text-align:left;}}\n*'''Cameron''' ''(labeled the \"Wide-Eyed Bubble Boy\")''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.freshtvinc.com/blog/total-drama-character-profiles-cameron/ |title=Total Drama Character Profiles - Cameron - Fresh TV |publisher=Freshtvinc.com |date=January 28, 2014 |accessdate=February 27, 2015}}</ref> is a close reference to [[Steve Urkel]]. He is a highly-intelligent, but physically-weak boy who spent most of his early life trapped inside a bubble. Initially he was quite timid and cowardly, and was tormented by several bullies on the show, however, he later learns to stand up for himself and prevails against them all. He was the original winner for the previous season, ''Total Drama: Revenge of the Island''. This season, he is quite often mistaken as a previous contestant, Cody, when interacting with Sierra. Voiced by Kevin Duhaney.\n*'''Jo''' ''(labeled the \"Take-No-Prisoners Machine\")''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.freshtvinc.com/blog/total-drama-character-profiles-jo/ |title=Total Drama Character Profiles - Jo - Fresh TV |publisher=Freshtvinc.com |date=March 19, 2014 |accessdate=February 27, 2015}}</ref> is based off [[Jane Lynch]] from ''[[Glee (TV series)|Glee]]'' when she was sixteen. She has a domineering, leadership personality and loves to take charge. She is mostly seen with male traits, even though she is female. Voiced by Laurie Elliot.\n*'''Lightning''' ''(labeled the \"Over-Achieving Athlete\")''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.freshtvinc.com/blog/total-drama-character-profiles-lightning/ |title=Total Drama Character Profiles - Lightning - Fresh TV |publisher=Freshtvinc.com |date=April 1, 2014 |accessdate=February 27, 2015}}</ref> is a close reference to [[Smash Williams]] from ''[[Friday Night Lights (TV series)|Friday Night Lights]]'', or [[Cuba Gooding, Jr.|Cuba Gooding]] Jr. from ''[[Jerry Maguire]]''. He is a super fit, [[National Football League|NFL]]-bound athlete and is one of the finalists of the previous season. However, Lightning is arrogant. He is always talking about himself, dimwitted, and he never supports anyone on his team. He always talks by adding \"sha-\" to the beginning of a word, which makes him annoying for other characters. Voiced by Tyrone Savage.\n*'''Sam''' ''(labeled the \"Nice Guy Gamer\")''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.freshtvinc.com/blog/total-drama-character-profiles-sam/ |title=Total Drama Character Profiles - Sam - Fresh TV |publisher=Freshtvinc.com |date=February 5, 2014 |accessdate=February 27, 2015}}</ref> is a [[Seth Rogen]]-type of character who spends most of his time playing video games. He thinks the whole world around him is a large video game, and references various real-life elements to his games. Voiced by Brian Froud.\n*'''Scott''' ''(labeled the \"Devious\")''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.freshtvinc.com/blog/total-drama-character-profiles-scott/ |title=Total Drama Character Profiles - Scott - Fresh TV |publisher=Freshtvinc.com |date=April 3, 2014 |accessdate=February 27, 2015}}</ref> is a devious and sneaky farm-boy, serving as the main antagonist of ''Total Drama: Revenge of the Island''. He is very mean, sneaky, and a liar who does whatever dirty deed it takes to win. His tactic in Total Drama: Revenge of the Island was to sabotage his own team without getting caught, which caused his teams to lose every single elimination challenge before the merge. He is somewhat of a bully to Cameron. People didn't realize that he was mean until the end of the series. Scott has a very large conflict with a mutated shark called Fang who constantly tries to brutally attack him any chance he gets for taking possession of one of Fang's shark teeth in Season 4. As a result, by the time of the Season 4 finale, Scott was hated and seen as a villain by every castmate including Chris. In Season 5, Scott returned as a member of the Villainous Vultures, serving as the comic relief of the season. He later gets into a relationship with Courtney, but soon ends it. He has orange hair, blue eyes, freckles, rosy cheeks, and long muscular arms. He wears a white tank top, long dark blue ankle-length pants, a dark grey belt with a silver buckle, and brown shoes. Voiced by James Wallis.\n{{hidden end}}\nOut of all the fourteen contestants, half are male and half are female. Seven of them are part of the first generation cast who have all been in ''Total Drama World Tour'', while the other seven are part of the second generation cast who have all competed in ''Total Drama: Revenge of the Island'' (the seven being the highest ranking for their season). Out of the seven original contestants, only Alejandro and Sierra have competed in one previous season; the other five have all competed in the first three seasons before ''Total Drama All-Stars''.\n\n===''Total Drama Pahkitew Island''===\n[[File:TDCast3.png|thumb|right|These are the fourteen new characters that were introduced in the second part of this season.<br />''Listed from left to right in order:''<br />'''Standing:''' Beardo, Max, Scarlett, Dave, Ella, Shawn (French Canadian winner), Sugar, Leonard<br />'''Sitting:''' Sky (English Canadian winner), Jasmine, Samey, Amy, Topher, Rodney]]\nPrevious contestants from past seasons do not compete in ''Total Drama Pahkitew Island'' because this part of the season features an entire new cast.<ref name=\"teletoon\" /> This is the second time the series completely replaces any existing cast with an all new cast, the previous time being in ''[[Total Drama: Revenge of the Island]]''. There are fourteen contestants as seen in an official season promo.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.teletoonmedia.com/en/images/thumbs/Pahkitew_Promo_Poster2-THUMB.JPG|title=Promo Poster|format=JPG|publisher=teletoonmedia.com|accessdate=December 7, 2013}}</ref> The new characters competing are Amy, Beardo, Dave, Ella, Jasmine, Leonard, Max, Rodney, Samey, Scarlett, Shawn, Sky, Sugar, and Topher.<ref name=\"s6cha\">{{cite web|url=https://www.scribd.com/doc/172602730/Total-Drama-Phakitew-Island-Season-5-Ep-105-Uh-So-This-is-My-Team-Act-II |accessdate=June 10, 2014 }}{{dead link|date=July 2018|bot=medic}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}{{citation needed|date=December 2013}}</ref> In October 2013, the second half of the first episode was leaked, revealing Beardo was the first to be eliminated.\n\n====Main characters====\nMain characters appear in every episode of the segment they compete in:\n*'''Shawn''', known as the ''zombie conspiracy nut'',<ref name=\"tdpi.voices\">{{cite web |url=http://www.freshtvinc.com/blog/total-drama-pahkitew-island-cast/ |title=Total Drama Pahkitew Island Cast List - Fresh TV |publisher=Freshtvinc.com |date=June 25, 2014 |accessdate=February 27, 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150629065742/http://www.freshtvinc.com/blog/total-drama-pahkitew-island-cast/ |archivedate=June 29, 2015 |df=mdy-all }}</ref> is an eccentric homeschooled boy. Growing up he did too much zombie stuff leading him to be paranoid about zombies. In fact, he believes the world has already succumbed to a [[zombie apocalypse]] and signed up to ''Total Drama'' as he believed residing on an island would increase his chances of survival. He becomes involved with a relationship with Jasmine. His character is a close reference to the main character of the movie, ''[[Shaun of the Dead]]'' (with his name also mixed with ''[[Dawn of the Dead (1978 film)|Dawn of the Dead]]''), while his appearance and personality is similar to that of Jude Lizowski from ''[[6teen]]'' (another one of Fresh TV's shows). Later, this was shown is the United States. Shawn won. He got Jasmine mad because he did not believe in her dream. So to get back with her he shares the money with her and uses his half to make a zombie bunker. Voiced by Zachary Bennett.\n*'''Sky''', known as ''the athlete'',<ref name=\"tdpi.voices\" /> is a kind, athletic, sports girl. She is the first female winner to win in Canada, the country of origin, although she only won in the English version. She is a natural-born leader and pulls the team through many challenges. Dave has a crush on her, which Sky originally did not share, however over time the feeling became mutual. Despite this Sky still values winning the competition over a relationship, the two are currently on uneasy terms. In the first episode it's possible that she is fluent in Cree as she rightly translated the team names. Voiced by Sarah Podemski.\n\n====Other characters====\nTwo of the characters, Amy and Samey, are twins, being the first time where related contestants compete in a season together.<ref name=\"ca.linkedin.com\">{{cite web |url=http://ca.linkedin.com/pub/bryn-mcauley/85/510/316 |title=Bryn McAuley &#124; LinkedIn |publisher=Ca.linkedin.com |accessdate=February 27, 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20140628224008/http://ca.linkedin.com/pub/bryn-mcauley/85/510/316 |archivedate=June 28, 2014 |df=mdy-all }}</ref> Scarlett is the first character in the new cast to have her final design revealed.<ref name=\"instas6\">{{cite web|url=http://www.instagram.com/p/i1-SCcvByk/ |title=Instagram |publisher=Instagram |date= |accessdate=February 27, 2015}}</ref> Unlike the first part of the season, the second part of the season will feature no cameos, meaning that any previous contestants will not be seen for the entire season's segment.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://thefreshchannel.tumblr.com/post/76545840004/ik-the-old-cast-isnt-in-pahkitew-but-are-they-ever |title=ik the old cast isn't in pahkitew but are they...|publisher=Thefreshchannel.tumblr.com |date=February 13, 2014 |accessdate=February 27, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://thefreshchannel.tumblr.com/post/76542786218/so-since-total-drama-pahkitew-island-is-going-to-be |title=So since Total Drama: Pahkitew Island is going to...|publisher=Thefreshchannel.tumblr.com |date=February 13, 2014 |accessdate=February 27, 2015}}</ref>\n{{hidden begin|title=List of characters|titlestyle=text-align:left;}}\n*'''Amy'''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cartoonnetwork.com/tv_shows/total-drama-auditions/video/amys-audition-clip.html |title=Amy's Audition - Total Drama Videos \u2013 Cartoon Network |publisher=Cartoonnetwork.com |date= |accessdate=February 27, 2015}}</ref> and '''Samey'''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cartoonnetwork.com/tv_shows/total-drama-auditions/video/sameys-audition-clip.html |title=Samey's Audition - Total Drama Videos \u2013 Cartoon Network |publisher=Cartoonnetwork.com |date= |accessdate=February 27, 2015}}</ref> known as the ''cheerleader twins'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.freshtvinc.com/blog/total-drama-pahkitew-island-rotations-amy-and-samey/ |title=Total Drama Pahkitew Island Rotations: Amy and Samey - Fresh TV |publisher=Freshtvinc.com |date=June 28, 2014 |accessdate=February 27, 2015}}</ref> are identical twin sisters, who are also the first related contestants in the series. Despite their similar looks, both sisters have very different personalities; one acts nice but is selfish in reality, while another is genuinely nice. They do not get along well with each other, since Amy was born 17 minutes before Samey. Amy believes she is the smarter one because of this, and thinks Samey is doing everything wrong. Because of this, Amy [[Sibling abuse|domestically abuses]] Samey and even attempts to [[Sororicide|kill]] her once in the premiere. Both voiced by Bryn McAuley.\n*'''Beardo''', known as the ''human soundboard'',<ref name=\"tdpi.voices\" /> is a close reference to [[Reggie Watts]] and [[Michael Winslow]]. He is a big fellow, with a noticeably large amount of facial hair. Being quite shy, he predominantly communicates via beat-boxing and other sound effects. Voiced by Cle Bennett.\n*'''Dave''', known as the ''normal guy'',<ref name=\"tdpi.voices\" /> is a nice normal guy, except he is extremely paranoid. Being a severe [[hypochondriac]] and [[germaphobia|germaphobe]], and is frequently seen rubbing disinfectant on himself. He has feelings for Sky until later in the finale when Chris turns Dave against Sky. Voiced by Daniel DeSanto.\n*'''Ella''', known as the ''fairytale princess'',<ref name=\"tdpi.voices\" /> is a close reference to one of the [[Disney Princess]] stereotypes, Snow White. She was in love with the fact that in [[Total Drama World Tour]], everyone had to sing in every episode. She is despised by Sugar even though she doesn't know that she hates her. She had a crush on Dave after he helped her put her shoe back on her foot after it fell in the water after a challenge and said that was a true fairytale moment. Voiced by Sunday Muse.\n*'''Jasmine''', known as the ''outback survivalist'',<ref name=\"tdpi.voices\" /> is an unusually tall Aboriginal Australian girl, who is tough and commandeering. She becomes deeply romantically involved with Shawn. She is often [[stereotype]]d by Chris McLean as he taunts her with \"[[outback]]\" jokes. She is also a close reference to a female counterpart of [[Steve Irwin]]. Voiced by Katie Bergin.\n*'''Leonard''', known as ''the LARPer'',<ref>http://www.cartoonnetwork.com/tv_shows/total-drama-auditions/video/leaonards-audition-clip.html</ref> is a guy who always dresses up as a wizard and tries to perform fake magic tricks. He returns as a contestant in the spin-off series, ''[[Total Drama Presents: The Ridonculous Race|The Ridonculous Race]]'', with his friend Tammy. Voiced by Cle Bennett.\n*'''Max''', known as the ''wannabe super-villain'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cartoonnetwork.com/tv_shows/total-drama-auditions/video/maxs-audition-clip.html |title=Max's Audition - Total Drama Videos \u2013 Cartoon Network |publisher=Cartoonnetwork.com |date= |accessdate=February 27, 2015}}</ref> is a parody of the super-villain stereotype, especially of [[Dr. Evil]] from the [[Austin Powers (film series)|Austin Powers]] franchise. He is a villain wannabe, who dreams of taking over the world. He prides in being evil, and views himself as dwarfing all other villains on Total Drama before him, however in reality he is one of the most incompetent villains to date. In the episode \"Three Zones and a Baby\" Max is shown to love [[babies]] when he's seen calming down a crying baby before the challenge and was doing baby talk throughout the challenge. Voiced by Bruce Dow.\n*'''Rodney''', known as the ''country boy'',<ref name=\"tdpi.voices\" /> is a gentle giant and muscular farm-boy with a huge heart and rosy cheeks. He's very shy, quiet, cute, sweet and handsome, and is usually seen blushing. He also doesn't talk very much. In fact he falls in love with a new girl in every episode, having fallen for Jasmine, Scarlett, and Amy, but never really admitting whom he likes a lot more than the other. He has fair skin, freckles, orange hair, and a large cleft chin. He wears navy blue ankle-length overalls with yellow buckles, a stomach pocket, side pockets, and light blue bottom edges over a white shirt with gray streaks covering his neck and red and white sneakers. He is also a close reference to [[Wreck-It Ralph]] and [[Johnny Cash]]. Voiced by Ian Ronningen.\n*'''Scarlett''', known as the ''quiet brainiac'',<ref name=\"tdpi.voices\" /> is a very smart girl who likes to help her team with her intelligence. Although she is first seen being kind-hearted to others, she eventually reveals herself as malevolent evil being who connived to take the million dollars from Chris over the other contestant's lives. She's the main antagonist in this season. Voiced by Kristi Friday.\n*'''Sugar''', known as the ''pageant Queen'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cartoonnetwork.com/tv_shows/total-drama-auditions/video/sugars-audition-clip.html |title=Sugar's Audition - Total Drama Videos \u2013 Cartoon Network |publisher=Cartoonnetwork.com |date= |accessdate=February 27, 2015}}</ref> is a close reference to [[Honey Boo Boo]]. She is a former beauty pageant queen who feels that the spotlight always needs to be on her. She eats a lot, and can lash out easily or cause the distrust of others. She had a strong hatred of Ella because of her constant singing and fairy tale princess personality. She speaks with a [[Southern American]] accent. Voiced by Rochelle Wilson.\n*'''Topher''', known as the ''Chris wannabe'',<ref name=\"tdpi.voices\" /> is Chris McLean's No. 1 Fan, and wishes to be just like him, down to his sadistic nature. He frequently gives suggestions to Chris on how to make the challenges even more painful, and is dying to be Chris's replacement. Voiced by Christopher Jacot.\n{{hidden end}}\n\n===Teams===\nJust like the previous four seasons, all of the characters depicted as contestants are split into two teams for each segment:\n\n====All Stars teams====\nAll the fourteen heroes and villains in ''Total Drama All-Stars'' are separated evenly into two teams. The first team is called the Heroic Hamsters, which consists of heroes while the second team is called the Villainous Vultures, which consists of villains.<ref name=\"animation\" /><ref name=\"insta.dn\" /> There were seven contestants in Team Heroes and seven on Team Villains.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cartoonnetwork.com/tv_shows/total-drama/preview/index.html |title=Total Drama Previews &#124; Watch Episode Previews and Discuss |publisher=Cartoon Network |date= |accessdate=February 27, 2015}}</ref> Here are the original members of each team, as of Episode 1:\n*'''Heroic Hamsters:''' Cameron, Courtney, Lindsay, Mike, Sam, Sierra, and Zoey.<ref name=\"cnallstars\" /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gjrLoHtxotY |title=Preview for \"Total Drama All-Stars\" |publisher=YouTube |date=August 28, 2013 |accessdate=February 27, 2015}}</ref>\n*'''Villainous Vultures:''' Alejandro, Duncan, Gwen, Heather, Jo, Lightning, and Scott.<ref name=\"cnallstars\" />\nIn Episode 3, \"Saving Private Leechball\", both Duncan and Courtney switch teams due to the former's heroic actions and the latter's villainous actions during the episode's challenge. In Episode 5, \"Moon Madness\", Cameron tried to vote himself out, but Chris wouldn't let him so Chris switched Cameron instead to the Villainous Vultures (despite Cameron not being a villain).\n\n==== Pahkitew Island teams ====\nThere are two teams in ''Total Drama: Pahkitew Island'' (both in the [[Cree]] language) which are Pim\u00e2potew Kinosewak (''translation: Floating Salmon'') and Waneyihtam Maskwak (''translation: Confused Bears''),<ref name=\"cree\">{{cite web |url=http://www.freshtvinc.com/blog/pahkitew-island-pronounce-pahkitew/ |title=Total Drama Pahkitew Island: How To Pronounce 'Pahkitew' - Fresh TV |publisher=Freshtvinc.com |date=June 13, 2014 |accessdate=February 27, 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150629062223/http://www.freshtvinc.com/blog/pahkitew-island-pronounce-pahkitew/ |archivedate=June 29, 2015 |df=mdy-all }}</ref> both of which have seven contestants with a team logo, which is either a green salmon logo or a red bear logo. Here are the original members for each team:\n*'''Pim\u00e2potew Kinosewak:''' Amy, Jasmine, Max, Rodney, Samey, Scarlett, and Topher.<ref name=\"s6cha\" />\n*'''Waneyihtam Maskwak:''' Beardo, Dave, Ella, Leonard, Shawn, Sky, and Sugar.<ref name=\"s6cha\" />\nMax and Sky switched teams in Episode 7, \"This is the Pits!\", instead of there being an elimination.\n\n===Cameos===\nIn July 2013, Cartoon Network started airing season promos that introduced non-competitors like Ezekiel, Izzy, and Owen. Even though they never competed in ''All-Stars'', these characters still went on to have [[cameo appearance]]s in the season.\n\nA list of all the cameos in ''Total Drama All-Stars'' and their roles during their cameos are shown below:\n{{hidden begin|title=List of cameos|titlestyle=text-align:left;}}\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center;width:100%\"\n|-\n! Episode\n! Character\n! style=\"width:120px\"| Voice actor\n! Role\n|-\n| '''1'''\n| Ezekiel\n| [[Peter Oldring]]\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| He is first seen being dropped from the helicopter by Chef, and is introduced as the fourteenth contestant of the season. Just as the deranged Ezekiel is about to fall on the other contestants, Chris states that he was only kidding about him being a contestant.\n|-\n| '''2'''\n| Blaineley\n| N/A\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| She is seen dating Bruno the bear in Paris on a boat that ran over Lightning, while he was distracted. (Canada only).\n|-\n| '''7'''\n| Izzy\n| [[Katie Crown]]\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| Izzy appears in \"Suckers Punched\", still dressed in a spider costume. She was intended to be the opponent for Cameron but Chris promised a random chance so she fought Mal (who is pretending to be Mike) instead. She isn't shown leaving the island, so her fate is unknown.\n|-\n| '''9'''\n| Ezekiel\n| Peter Oldring\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| Ezekiel appears while kidnapping Chris with the 100th Episode anniversary cake. The merged campers then have to search for him inside his mystery mine. He isn't seen leaving the island, so his fate is unknown.\n|-\n| '''13'''\n| Owen\n| [[Scott McCord]]\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| He appears briefly while inflating the balloons used to place the eliminated contestants in, being his usual happy self. Owen later appears water skiing at the end of the episode, saying a shout-out to his mother. Owen was the last character to be seen in the season.\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| '''Various'''\n| Mr. Coconut\n| N/A\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| Mr. Coconut makes a brief cameo in the intro of every episode. He also appeared in the heater of the cabins, while Cameron was searching in \"Zeek and Ye Shall Find\". He made his final appearance in \"The Final Wreck-ening\", on the weapons rack that Chris unveils.\n|-\n| Cody\n| [[Kevin Duhaney]]<br />(as Cameron)\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| Cody was seen and animated during various brief cameos, even though he was still not physically there. Sierra also referenced Cody several times during her time in the competition. She hallucinates her teammates, Cameron as Cody in \u201cSaving Private Leechball\u201d, and Duncan, Mike, Sam, and Zoey as Cody in \u201cFood Fright\u201d. After Sierra's elimination (Canadian clip only), she is sent to [[Area 51]] where she witnesses a cloning station that created many new Cody copies.\n|}\n* '''Note:''' Dakota was also seen in a photograph which was shown by Sam.\n{{hidden end}}\nThere are no cameos in ''Total Drama: Pahkitew Island'' as no characters from previous seasons are seen in this segment. The only reference to an original character is Cody's shoe in the episode, \"Mo' Monkey, Mo' Problems\".\n\n==Production==\nOn June 28, 2011, [[Christian Potenza]] mentioned an upcoming season of ''[[Total Drama]]''. This was the first time a cast member mentioned a fifth season to the public.<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XIhRjeVniZM Skip to 8:55]</ref> One year later on July 19, 2012, [[Christian Potenza]] announced a fifth season of ''[[Total Drama]]'' in an interview with [[Tom McGillis]], saying that Season 5 will be just like Seasons 1 and 4.<ref name=\"mcgillis.interview\">{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Q3zV1d_WCC8 |title=Season 5 is Coming! |publisher=Youtube.com |date=July 19, 2012 |accessdate=October 16, 2012}}</ref> This hinted that this season will take place back at an island.\n\nAs shown in the [[Fresh TV]] official Website, it seems that there will be 26 new episodes to be aired in 2013\u20132014 for Season 5.<ref name=\"s5\">{{cite web |url=http://freshtvinc.com/content/index.asp?page=15 |title=Fresh TV reveals number of episodes for Season 5 |publisher=Freshtvinc.com |accessdate=October 16, 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121125141456/http://freshtvinc.com/content/index.asp?page=15 |archivedate=November 25, 2012 |df=mdy-all }}</ref> Tom McGillis later stated that the new 26 episodes will be split into two 13-episode seasons; where the first part will feature some of existing cast, while the second part will consist of only new cast which are yet to be introduced.<ref name=\"s5confirmed\" /> Voice actors began recording lines for Season 5 in December 2012.\n\n===''Total Drama All-Stars''===\nOn January 28, 2013, [[Cartoon Network]] confirmed that the new season title will be ''Total Drama All-Stars'' for Part 1.<ref name=\"upfront\">http://www.streetinsider.com/Press+Releases/Cartoon+Network+Gets+In+Front+of+the+Upfront/8034926.html</ref> One day later on January 30, both Christian Potenza and Drew Nelson confirmed the title for Episode 4 which is \"Food Fright\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.facebook.com/photo.php?fbid=10152459894935338&set=a.10150434372575338.630062.834770337&type=1&relevant_count=1 |title=Mobile Uploads - Christian Potenza |publisher=Facebook |date= |accessdate=February 27, 2015}}</ref> Drew Nelson also confirmed that the two new teams for this season are the Heroic Hamsters and the Villainous Vultures.<ref name=\"insta.dn\">{{cite web|url=http://instagram.com/p/VHoKWjxrF6/ |title=Instagram |publisher=Instagram |date= |accessdate=February 27, 2015}}</ref> Rumors started floating in early 2010 about the season being \"Heroes vs. Villains\" and that both the original and the new cast would compete together,<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WXQnIpeE5o8 Early talks about Season 5 in 2010]</ref> but it wasn't until December 19, 2012 when Tom McGillis confirmed on [[ABC3]] Australia that the theme for this season will indeed be \"Heroes vs. Villains\".\n\nOn February 1, 2013, Christian Potenza released a new video that contains several new information about ''Total Drama All-Stars'', including season episode titles, new voice actors, and plot information.<ref name=\"tdas.pt1\"/> That same day, Christian Potenza also released the first lines of the season from Episode 4:\n\n{{cquote|''When a Hero's eating time is up, they hear this ... and the Villains get this ... Last time on a very special episode of Total Drama All-Stars: ... Say hello to my metal friend! ... I sincerely doubt it, Al ... next, I'll allow it, his pain was our gain ... Which team will finish their barf-tastic breakfast first? Find out after the break on Total Drama All-Stars!''<ref name=\"tdas.pt1\" />}}\n\nOn June 11, 2013 it was confirmed that the airdate for the whole season will take place in early 2014; mostly during the winter of 2014.<ref name=\"teletoon\" /> Tom McGillis later confirmed on Twitter that the Canadian airdate will be in January 2014, while the U.S. airdate will be in September 2013.<ref name=\"tommcgillis\" /> On August 19, 2013, Cartoon Network released the first official trailer for TDAS along with a new website that reveals all the characters. Lindsay's and Jo's elimination were leaked via episode scripts and trailers long before the season started airing.\n\n===''Total Drama: Pahkitew Island''===\nAs for ''Total Drama: Pahkitew Island'', production is done and it has been released in the United States.<ref name=\"s5-100\" /> The season was first announced to air on May 27,<ref>Fresh TV (@thefreshchannel). \"[https://twitter.com/thefreshchannel/status/463836270423060480 #TotalDrama fans: #PahkitewIsland premiere slated for May 27th on Cartoon Network has been postponed. Stay tuned for updates.]\" Twitter. 00:22 May 7, 2014 (UTC). Retrieved May 10, 2014.</ref> but was later delayed to July 7.<ref name=\"toon.tdpi\" /> This part is under the same production code as the previous part, ''Total Drama All-Stars''.<ref name=\"mipcom\"/> However, the script for the entire first episode was leaked online about a year before the season's release.<ref name=\"s6cha\" /> Scarlett's final design along with one second of the fully animated first episode was also leaked on Instagram by her Venezuelan Spanish voice actor.<ref name=\"instas6\" />\n\nOn March 21, 2014, the entire cast design was revealed by Fresh TV along with new promotions for the season.<ref name=\"cakes6\">{{cite web|url=http://www.cakeentertainment.com/Brand/75 |title=Total Drama Pahkitew Island |publisher=Cakeentertainment.com |date= |accessdate=February 27, 2015}}</ref> [[Bryn McAuley]] who will be voicing the twins, Amy and Samey, was the first confirmed voice actress.<ref name=\"ca.linkedin.com\"/> On April 9, 2014, [[Fresh TV]] Inc. celebrated the [[International Day of Pink]] by making the TDPI cast all wear pink clothing, symbolizing the support for anti-bullying.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.freshtvinc.com/blog/international-day-of-pink/ |title=Total Drama Pahkitew Island Goes Pink for International Day of Pink! |publisher=Freshtvinc.com |date=April 8, 2014 |accessdate=February 27, 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402115444/http://www.freshtvinc.com/blog/international-day-of-pink/ |archivedate=April 2, 2015 |df=mdy-all }}</ref> Before the official cast release [[Sunday Muse]] was also confirmed to voice Ella,<ref name=\"voatlanta2014.com\">{{cite web |url=http://voatlanta2014.com/sunday-muse/ |title=Sunday Muse |publisher=VO Atlanta 2014 |accessdate=February 27, 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141006131213/http://voatlanta2014.com/sunday-muse/ |archivedate=October 6, 2014 |df=mdy-all }}</ref> while Ian Ronningen was set to voice Rodney.<ref name=\"ianronningen.workbooklive.com\">{{cite web|url=http://ianronningen.workbooklive.com/Wbl.mvc/Page/Resume |title=Ian Ronningen Resume Page |publisher=Ianronningen.workbooklive.com |date= |accessdate=February 27, 2015}}</ref> On May 30, 2014 a new teaser trailer was released for TDPI in Italy, marking the first time fully animated scenes were released to the public.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=na2uFfXoKyI |title=Total Drama: Pahkitew Island, Italian Trailer #1 WITH SUBTITLES |publisher=YouTube |date=May 31, 2014 |accessdate=February 27, 2015}}</ref> Several trailers in English were released later in Cake Entertainment's website. On June 16, Cartoon Network posted the Pahkitew Island website, along with the audition tapes for Sugar, Samey, Amy, Leonard, and Max.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cartoonnetwork.com/tv_shows/total-drama/video/episodes/index.html |title=Total Drama: Pahkitew Island &#124; Season 1 |publisher=Cartoonnetwork.com |date= |accessdate=February 27, 2015}}</ref> Italy was the first country to air full episodes for Pahkitew Island.<ref name=\"k2tv\">{{cite web |url=http://www.k2tv.it/serie/a-tutto-reality |title=A tutto reality: l'isola &#124; Stagione 1 &#124; Tutte le puntate &#124; Video &#124; K2 |publisher=K2tv.it |accessdate=February 27, 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140717122238/http://www.k2tv.it/serie/a-tutto-reality |archive-date=July 17, 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref> On June 23, the audition tapes of Beardo, Rodney, Ella, Topher, and Dave were released. On June 26, the entire cast and the characters they voiced were released via Fresh's re:fresh blog.<ref name=\"tdpi.voices\" /> On July 1, ABC3 announced that ''Total Drama: Pahkitew Island'' will air July 14, 2014 in Australia.<ref name=\"abc\" />\nAPTN network November 30 to December 30, 2015\n\n==Reception==\n{{expand section|date=March 2014}}\n\n===Ratings===\n''Total Drama All-Stars'' was the #1 telecast on Cartoon Network with the highest ratings for the week of the season premiere.<ref>{{cite web|author=Son of the Bronx on |url=http://sonofthebronx.blogspot.com/2013/09/cartoon-network-ratings-september-9-15.html |title=Son of the Bronx: Cartoon Network ratings (September 9-15, 2013) |publisher=Sonofthebronx.blogspot.com |date=September 21, 2013 |accessdate=February 27, 2015}}</ref> Additionally, it ranked as the #1 telecast on all television among boys 6\u201311 and 9\u201314 for Tuesday prime-time airings. It also claimed #1 in its 7 p.m. time period among kids 9\u201314 and boys 6\u201311 and 9\u201314.<ref name=\"toon.tdpi\" />\n\n===Critical reaction===\n''Total Drama All Stars'' has received mixed or average reviews. Many claimed there was \"character derailment\" within the new and old cast of characters. It currently holds a 5.4 rating on Metacritic based on 9 reviews.<ref>http://www.metacritic.com/tv/total-drama-island/season-5</ref> ''Total Drama: Pahkitew Island'', however, was considerably more positive. The season currently holds a 73% approval rating according to Rotten Tomatoes.<ref>https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/total-drama-island-season-1/reviews/</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* ''[[Total Drama Island]]'' (the original set of contestants)\n* ''[[Total Drama: Revenge of the Island]]'' (the first time a new cast was introduced)\n{{portal bar|Animation|Television|Canada}}\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Wikiquote}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20150206070400/http://www.teletoon.com/en/tv/totalDramaAllStars Official TDAS site on Teletoon]\n* [http://www.cakeentertainment.com/Brand/75 TDPI Promotional Article] Cake Entertainment\n\n{{Total Drama}}\n\n[[Category:Total Drama seasons]]\n[[Category:2010s Canadian animated television series]]\n[[Category:2010s Canadian satirical television series]]\n[[Category:Canadian children's animated comedy television series]]\n[[Category:Canadian flash animated television series]]\n[[Category:Canadian mockumentary television series]]\n[[Category:2014 Canadian television seasons]]\n[[Category:Split television seasons]]\n[[Category:Television series produced in Toronto]]\n", "text_old": "{{About|the fifth season|the entire series|Total Drama}}\n{{DISPLAYTITLE:''Total Drama All-Stars'' and ''Pahkitew Island''}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=February 2015}}\n{{Infobox television season\n| italic_title = no\n| bgcolour     = orange\n| image        = [[File:Total Drama All-Stars logo.svg|250px]]<br />[[File:Total Drama Pahkitew logo.png|250px]]\n| image_alt    = \n| caption      = ''Top'': logo for ''Total Drama All-Stars''<br />''Bottom'': logo for ''Total Drama Pahkitew Island''\n| country      = Canada\n| num_episodes = 26<ref name=\"s5fresh\" /><ref name=\"teletoon\" />\n| network      = [[Teletoon]]\n| first_aired  = {{Start date|2014|1|9}}\n| last_aired   = {{End date|2014|11|20}}\n| prev_season  = ''[[Total Drama: Revenge of the Island]]''\n| next_season  = ''[[Total Drama Presents: The Ridonculous Race]]'' (spin-off)\n| episode_list = List of Total Drama episodes\n}}\n'''''Total Drama All-Stars''''' and '''''Total Drama Pahkitew Island''''' are two different seasons that have 13-episode segments that both make up the fifth and final season of the Canadian [[animated television series]], ''[[Total Drama]]''. The season was commissioned by [[Cartoon Network]] in October 2012, ordering 26 episodes.<ref name=\"s5confirmed\">[http://www.freshtvinc.com/blog/mipcom-news-with-tom-mcgillis/ MIPCOM News with Tom McGillis!] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140405050531/http://www.freshtvinc.com/blog/mipcom-news-with-tom-mcgillis/ |date=April 5, 2014 }}</ref> It is a sequel to ''[[Total Drama Island]]'', ''[[Total Drama Action]]'', ''[[Total Drama World Tour]]'', and ''[[Total Drama: Revenge of the Island]]''. The season was produced by [[Fresh TV]] and the [[Aboriginal Peoples Television Network]]<ref name=\"atpn\">{{cite web|url=http://www.freshtvinc.com/news/total-drama-pahkitew-island-debuts-on-aptn/ |title=Fresh TV - Total Drama: Pahkitew Island Debuts on APTN |publisher=Freshtvinc.com |date=January 10, 2015 |accessdate=February 27, 2015}}</ref> and distributed by [[Cake Entertainment]]. Owing to the series' premise, the season presents itself as a parody of [[reality television]] series, such as ''[[Survivor (TV series)|Survivor]]''.<ref name=\"mcgillis.interview\" />\n\nThe entire season first premiered in the United States starting on September 10, 2013 on Cartoon Network with the first part,<ref name=\"usaairdate\">{{cite web|url=http://www.worldscreen.com/articles/display/2013-8-9-kid-cartoon-network-total-drama-all-stars |title=Archives |publisher=WorldScreen.com |date= |accessdate=February 27, 2015}}</ref> while the second part premiered in the United States on July 7, 2014 for a two-week time period.<ref name=\"toon.tdpi\" /> In Canada, the first part premiered on [[Teletoon]] during their \"Can't Miss Thursdays\" time slot starting January 9, 2014,<ref name=\"tdascandate\">{{cite web|url=http://www.teletoonmedia.com/en/index.php/teletoon/highlight/category/january_2014_programming_highlights |title=Corus M\u00e9dia |publisher=Teletoonmedia.com |date= |accessdate=February 27, 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"tommcgillis\">[https://www.twitter.com/tommcgillis/status/345897902918496257 Date of Release Announced for Total Drama All-Stars!]</ref> while the second part of the season also premiered during their \"Can't Miss Thursdays\" time slot on Teletoon starting on September 4, 2014.<ref name=\"can.air\" /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.freshtvinc.com/blog/total-drama-pahkitew-island-recaps-episode-1/ |title=Total Drama Pahkitew Island Recaps - Fresh TV |publisher=Freshtvinc.com |date=September 5, 2014 |accessdate=February 27, 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"s5-100\">{{cite web|url=http://us1.campaign-archive2.com/?u=3de38b7dddbafe3fa262c2b48&id=bd85d0592b |title=Total Drama Celebrates Its 100th Episode |publisher=Us1.campaign-archive2.com |date=February 25, 2014 |accessdate=February 27, 2015}}</ref> The second half of the season also premiered on the APTN network in 2015.<ref name=\"atpn\" />\n\n==Synopsis==\nJust like ''Total Drama: Revenge of the Island'' before it, this season also consists of 13 episode segments;<ref name=\"s5fresh\">[http://freshtvinc.com/content/index.asp?page=15 Fresh TV reveals number of episodes for Season 5] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121125141456/http://freshtvinc.com/content/index.asp?page=15 |date=November 25, 2012 }}</ref> even though it brings back the traditional 26-episode length of the first three seasons. The winning characters for part 1 are either Mike or Zoey, and the winning characters for part 2 are either Shawn or Sky (depending on the countries the season finale airs). The total grand prize for this season is C$2 million, which is split in half across both parts.\n\n===Part 1===\n'''''Total Drama All-Stars''''' is the first part of the season. [[Christian Potenza]] first announced the season in an interview with [[Tom McGillis]] (the creator of the series), saying that ''Total Drama All-Stars'' would be very similar to ''[[Total Drama Island]]'' and ''[[Total Drama: Revenge of the Island]]'', due to the high worldwide ratings of the latter.<ref name=\"mcgillis.interview\" /> That means that this part of the season takes place back at Camp Wawanakwa; in a single location once again, unlike ''[[Total Drama World Tour]]''. This part is also very similar to the previous season, ''[[Total Drama: Revenge of the Island]]'' (both being very similar in terms of length, location, features and cameos).\n\nThis half is an [[all-star]] season which features a return of fourteen of the strongest contestants from both the first and second generation cast.<ref name=\"s5confirmed\" /><ref name=\"animation\">{{cite web|author=Ramin Zahed |url=http://www.animationmagazine.net/tv/total-drama-all-stars-ready-to-shine-on-cn/ |title='Total Drama All-Stars' Ready to Shine on CN |publisher=Animation Magazine |date=August 8, 2013 |accessdate=February 27, 2015}}</ref> This is the first season to feature characters from two different generations competing together. The theme for this season is \"Heroes vs. Villains\" which means the competitors were separated into teams based on their past performance; with Heroes\" from each season having to face off against each season's \"Villains\".<ref name=\"upfront\" /> Both the season's first title, \"[[Survivor: All-Stars|All-Stars]]\" and the \"[[Survivor: Heroes vs. Villains|Heroes vs. Villains]]\" theme take after respective seasons from ''Survivor''.\n\nCartoon Network's official synopsis describes the first part, ''Total Drama All-Stars'' as:\n{{cquote|''Total Drama is back, but this time the team at Fresh TV have assembled the best loved and most hated contestants from seasons past to compete&nbsp;\u2013 Heroes vs. Villains style!''<ref name=\"upfront\" />}}\n\n===Part 2===\n[[File:TDisland2.png|thumb|right|A brand new island is used again for this season. This is the first new main location in the series since ''[[Total Drama Action]]''.]]\n\n'''''Total Drama Pahkitew Island''''' is the second part of the 26 episodes that Cartoon Network ordered in 2012 for the fifth season. It was first announced on June 11, 2013 as a sixth season, even though it is still part of Season 5.<ref name=\"teletoon\">{{cite web|url=http://www.newswire.ca/en/story/1181701/inspector-gadget-reboot-tops-off-teletoon-canada-s-latest-original-production-slate |title=Inspector Gadget Reboot Tops Off TELETOON Canada's Latest Original Production Slate|publisher=Newswire.ca |date=June 11, 2013 |accessdate=December 7, 2013}}</ref> This part features an entire new cast considered as the third generation of ''Total Drama'' characters and takes place at a brand new island, due to Chef Hatchet using a [[land drill]] to sink Camp Wawanakwa in the episode, \"The Final Wreck-ening\". This new island is the first new main setting in the series since ''[[Total Drama Action]]''.\n\nPart 2 aired in North America throughout the second half of 2014, but Italy was the first country to air ''Total Drama Pahkitew Island'' starting on June 13, 2014.<ref name=\"k2tv\" /> This is the first season to air a new episode every day in the United States, and will also set the studio's record for fastest English airing for any season in the series.<ref name=\"toon.tdpi\" /> This part is being story edited by [[Terry McGurrin]], while Dennis Jackson and [[Melanie Jackson]], series creators of ''[[Wapos Bay: The Series]]'', also helped write and consult the plot for TDPI.<ref name=\"cree\" /> ''Total Drama: Pahkitew Island'' was sponsored by the [[Aboriginal Peoples Television Network]], who helped with the [[Cree]] translations for the team names and various season references.<ref name=\"cree\" />\n\nA general synopsis from Teletoon describes the second part, ''Total Drama: Pahkitew Island'' as:\n{{cquote|''It's an all-new season in an all-new location: Pahkitew Island. Given that the Cree word for \"explode\" is Pahkitew, it's no wonder that host Chris McLean chose this new island to put a fresh collection of victims&nbsp;\u2013 er, contestants&nbsp;\u2013 through the most grueling challenges yet. Once again teen freaks, geeks, egos, and cowards smash, crash, and bash their way through the season with one goal in mind: winning that one million dollar prize. Who will take it home? No one knows until the final episode drops and the pain finally stops.''<ref name=\"teletoons6\">{{cite web|url=http://www.newswire.ca/en/story/1181701/inspector-gadget-reboot-tops-off-teletoon-canada-s-latest-original-production-slate |title=TELETOON Canada Inc. &#124; Inspector Gadget Reboot Tops Off TELETOON Canada's Latest Original Production Slate |publisher=Newswire.ca |date=June 11, 2013 |accessdate=February 27, 2015}}</ref>}}\n\n==Plot==\nBoth parts feature a fictional titular reality show that follows the competition of fourteen animated teenagers at a fictional island. For ''Total Drama All-Stars'', the original island used in the first season is featured, where the producers say it is located somewhere in [[Muskoka]], [[Ontario]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.toynewsi.com/news.php?itemid=19834 |title=Cartoon Network Announces It's New & Returning Shows For 2013-2014 Season - What's In Store For DC Nation? - - Action Figures Toys News |publisher=Toynewsi.com |date=January 28, 2013 |accessdate=February 27, 2015}}</ref> The second part of the season, ''Total Drama: Pahkitew Island'', features a brand new island which producers say it is located somewhere in [[British Columbia|Western Canada]].<ref name=\"cakes6\" /> The season's animated characters are depicted as campers who participate in themed challenges and must avoid being voted off the island by other fellow campers. At the end of the series, the winning contestant or the last camper to stand on the island will win [[Canadian dollar|C$]]1,000,000. The competition is hosted by Chris McLean ([[Christian Potenza]]), who is assisted by the camp's chef, Chef Hatchet ([[Cl\u00e9 Bennett]]).<ref name=\"tv\">{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2013/08/08/total-drama-all-stars-to-premiere-tuesday-september-10-on-cartoon-network/196401/ |title='Total Drama All-Stars' to Premiere Tuesday, September 10 on Cartoon Network - Ratings |publisher=TVbytheNumbers.Zap2it.com |date=August 8, 2013 |accessdate=February 27, 2015}}</ref>\n\nAt the beginning of the competition, the fourteen campers are evenly placed into two teams which are themed to the genre of the competition. In each episode, the two teams participate in a challenge, in which one or more campers can win invincibility for their team. The losing team is called to the campfire at night, where they must vote one of their members off the island. The camper with the most votes is eliminated from the competition. At this campfire, McLean passes out marshmallows to the campers who have not been voted off, while the one who does not get a marshmallow is eliminated. That eliminated person must then walk to the island's dock and will be forced off of the island, and told to \"never, ever come back\", according to Chris.\n\nAbout halfway through the competition, the teams are disbanded, after which the challenges continue; the winner of each challenge then only receives invincibility for him or herself, whereupon a camper without invincibility is voted off the island. This process of elimination continues on until two players remains on the island. These two players, are now then subject to a final contest. At the end, a camper wins the competition, while the loser ends up being the runner-up. However, the runner-up is the winner in the other ending of the finale, as there are always two endings to ''[[Total Drama]]'' seasons. This season, along with every other season in the series, is a parody of the reality show ''[[Survivor (TV series)|Survivor]]'' while the host, Chris McLean is very similar to ''Survivor'' host [[Jeff Probst]] with the evil persona of [[Fear Factor]]{{'s}} [[Joe Rogan]].<ref name = \"monitor\">{{Citation| author = Aaron Sagers| title = Pop 20: If Facebook were a dinner party| newspaper = The Monitor| issue =| page =| date = September 1, 2009}}</ref>\n\n==Episodes==\n{{Main|List of Total Drama All-Stars and Pahkitew Island episodes}}\nThe first thirteen episodes is an all-star season using fourteen returning characters from the two previous seasons,<ref name=\"s5confirmed\" /> while the last thirteen episodes consist of a new cast introducing fourteen new characters.<ref name=\"teletoon\" /> Both halves are part of the 26 episodes that Cartoon Network ordered in 2012.<ref name=\"mipcom\">{{cite web|url=http://www.freshtvinc.com/blog/mipcom-news-with-tom-mcgillis|title=MIPCOM News with Tom McGillis|first=Julie|last=Giles|publisher=Freshtvinc.com |date=October 22, 2012|accessdate=December 7, 2013}}</ref> Cartoon Network aired the whole season first starting on September 10, 2013 on Tuesdays at 7:00&nbsp;p.m. [[Eastern Time Zone|EST]] in the United States,<ref name=\"usaairdate\" /> with Teletoon airing the season later on January 9, 2014 at 7:00&nbsp;p.m. EST.<ref name=\"tdascandate\" />\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;width:100%\"\n|-\n! style=\"background:orange\" rowspan=\"2\"| Season\n! style=\"background:orange\" rowspan=\"2\"| Episodes\n! style=\"background:orange\" rowspan=\"2\"| Country\n! style=\"background:orange\" rowspan=\"2\"| Network\n! style=\"background:orange\" colspan=\"2\"| Ep. 1\u201313: ''Total Drama All-Stars''\n! style=\"background:orange\" colspan=\"2\"| Ep. 14\u201326: ''Total Drama Pahkitew Island''\n|-\n! style=\"background:orange\"| Part 1 premiere\n! style=\"background:orange\"| Part 1 finale\n! style=\"background:orange\"| Part 2 premiere\n! style=\"background:orange\"| Part 2 finale\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\"| 5<ref name=\"upfront\" />\n| rowspan=\"4\"| 26<ref name=\"s5fresh\" /><ref name=\"teletoon\" />\n| Australia\n| [[ABC3]]\n| December 12, 2013<ref name=\"abc\">{{cite web|url=http://www.abc.net.au/abc3/shows/14898.htm |title=ABC3 - TV Program - Total Drama All Stars |publisher=Abc.net.au |date= |accessdate=February 27, 2015}}</ref>\n| December 30, 2013\n| July 14, 2014<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.abc.net.au/abc3/shows/guide/201407/20140714.htm |title=ABC3 TV Shows |publisher=Abc.net.au |date=July 14, 2014 |accessdate=February 27, 2015}}</ref>\n| October 6, 2014\n|-\n! Canada<!-- This is the original airing of the season -->\n! [[Teletoon]]\n! January 9, 2014<ref name=\"teletoon\" /><ref name=\"tommcgillis\" />\n! March 27, 2014\n! September 4, 2014<ref name=\"can.air\">{{cite web|url=http://www.worldscreen.com/articles/display/2014-7-8-kids-totaldrama-teletoon |title=Archives |publisher=WorldScreen.com |date= |accessdate=February 27, 2015}}</ref>\n! November 20, 2014<ref name=\"s5-100\" />\n|-\n| Italy<!-- Do not remove as it was the first worldwide airing of the season -->\n| [[K2 (TV channel)|K2]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.k2tv.it/programmi/a-tutto-reality-lisola-di-pahkitew/ |title=Nothing found for Programmi A Tutto Reality Lisola Di Pahkitew |publisher=K2tv.it |accessdate=February 27, 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160131054208/http://www.k2tv.it/programmi/a-tutto-reality-lisola-di-pahkitew/ |archive-date=January 31, 2016 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n| March 3, 2014\n| March 18, 2014\n| June 13, 2014<ref>{{YouTube|id=BF3Z1aCGDG0}}</ref>\n| June 27, 2014\n|-\n| United States<!-- This is the first English airing of the season -->\n| [[Cartoon Network]]\n| September 10, 2013<ref name=\"usaairdate\" />\n| December 3, 2013\n| July 7, 2014<ref name=\"toon.tdpi\">{{cite web |url=http://www.freshtvinc.com/news/cartoon-network-dishes-up-more-drama/ |title=Fresh TV - Cartoon Network Dishes Up More Drama! |publisher=Freshtvinc.com |accessdate=February 27, 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402093838/http://www.freshtvinc.com/news/cartoon-network-dishes-up-more-drama/ |archivedate=April 2, 2015 |df=mdy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cartoonnetwork.com/tv_shows/total-drama/video/brand-new-total-drama-coming-in-july-clip.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2014-06-22 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140622010914/http://www.cartoonnetwork.com/tv_shows/total-drama/video/brand-new-total-drama-coming-in-july-clip.html |archivedate=June 22, 2014 |df=mdy-all }}</ref>\n| July 18, 2014<ref name=\"toon.tdpi\" />\n|}\nThis season also features the 100th episode of the entire series which was aired in Canada on February 27, 2014.<ref name=\"s5-100\"/> The 100th episode of the series is the 9th episode of this season, \"Zeek and Ye Shall Find\". All episodes for the fifth season are 21 minutes and 20 seconds long, all of them much shorter than previous seasons. This is the first season to feature a 20-second intro, as every other previous season had a full one-minute intro section.\n\n==All Stars==\n\n===All Stars Staff===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" \n|-\n! Character\n! Voice actor\n! Description\n|-\n| {{va|Chris McLean}}\n| [[Christian Potenza]]\n| Chris returns as the host of the series.\n|-\n| {{va|Chef Hatchet}}\n| [[Cl\u00e9 Bennett]]\n| Hatchet returns as the cook and co-host of the series.\n|-\n|}\n\n===All Stars Contestants===\nThe contestant pool consists of 14 contestants. Seven from the third season and seven from the fourth season.\n\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"margin:auto; text-align:center\"\n|+List of ''Total Drama All-Stars'' contestants\n!align=\"left\"|Contestant\n!Original team\n!Switched team\n!Merge\n!Finish\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|'''Lindsay'''<br><small>The Dumb Princess</small>\n|{{stribe|pagong|Heroic Hamsters}}\n|bgcolor=\"darkgrey\"|\n|bgcolor=\"darkgrey\"|\n|{{sort|08|14th place}}\n|-\n| align=\"left\" |'''Lig